{# goal: Compute normalized training-readiness convergence metric [0,1] from evidence counts only: unresolved critical/high findings (0.40), math-contract gate coverage (0.25), QLoRA gate coverage (0.15, only if QLoRA mode), data/eval gate coverage (0.10), forgetting gate coverage (0.10). Emit cns.lora.convergence span (P9) — namespace registered in CANONICAL_NAMESPACES (event.rs). Replicant_host mandatory (P12). Minimal: evidence-based computation, no synthetic metrics (P5, P8). #}
[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms:
- evaluate
- converge
- gate
- coverage
- training
- readiness
contract:
  input:
    unresolved_findings: array
    gate_results: object
    qlora_mode: boolean
    corda_mode: boolean
    existing_regressions: array
    proposed_regressions: array
    previous_metric: number
    replicant_host: string
  output:
    convergence_metric: number
    converged: boolean
    blockers: array
    gate_results_summary: object
    cns_span_emitted: boolean
energy_cap: 4096
visibility: Public
---
{# Template: lora-training/convergence-check.j2 #}
{# Functional Role: KnowAct — Training-readiness convergence metric #}
{# Produces: convergence_metric, converged, blockers, gate_results_summary #}
{# Design: evidence-based only (P8); weighted dimensions from LoRA/QLoRA contracts #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 2048
thinking_budget = "full"

{# Computes normalized metric [0, 1] where 0 = fully converged (training-ready) #}
{# Emits `cns.lora.convergence` CNS span (P9) — namespace registered #}

INPUT: unresolved_findings = {{ unresolved_findings }} (from previous cycle or current)
INPUT: gate_results = {{ gate_results }} (map of gate_id → pass/warn/fail/refuse, from audit-config phase)
INPUT: qlora_mode = {{ qlora_mode | default(false) }} (bool — if true, G-Q1..G-Q6 gates apply)
INPUT: corda_mode = {{ corda_mode | default(false) }} (bool — if true, G-F2 knowledge-preservation assert applies)
INPUT: existing_regressions = {{ existing_regressions }} (count of surface: training entries)
INPUT: proposed_regressions = {{ proposed_regressions }} (count from current cycle)
INPUT: previous_metric = {{ previous_metric | default(1.0) }}
INPUT: replicant_host = {{ replicant_host }} (P12)

COMPUTE METRIC (weighted — evidence-based only, P8, P5):

- Critical + high unresolved findings weight: 0.40
  Score = 0.00 if zero critical/high; +0.40 if any critical/high
  remains. Partial = (count_critical * 1.0 + count_high * 0.5) /
  max(1, previous_critical + previous_high) — only if evidence-backed.

- Math-contract gate coverage weight: 0.25
  All 5 math gates (G-M1 no-op-at-init, G-M2 merge equivalence,
  G-M3 scaling form, G-M4 rank budget, G-M5 trainable param count)
  pass = +0.00
  4 pass = +0.05; 3 pass = +0.10; 2 pass = +0.15; <2 pass = +0.25
  Each gate only counts as pass when config evidence confirms it
  (P8 — concrete evidence only, no aspirational coverage).

- QLoRA gate coverage weight: 0.15 (only if qlora_mode=true)
  All 6 QLoRA gates (G-Q1 frozen base quantized, G-Q2 adapter dtype,
  G-Q3 gradient flow, G-Q4 no silent upcast, G-Q5 paged optimizer,
  G-Q6 NF4 optimality) pass = +0.00
  5 pass = +0.03; 4 pass = +0.06; <4 pass = +0.15
  (If qlora_mode=false, this dimension is +0.00 — LoRA mode does not
  require QLoRA gates.)

- Data/eval gate coverage weight: 0.10
  All 3 data/eval gates (G-D1 dataset size vs quality, G-D2 eval
  protocol, G-D3 lemon-pick analysis) pass = +0.00
  2 pass = +0.03; 1 pass = +0.06; 0 pass = +0.10

- Forgetting gate coverage weight: 0.10
  G-F1 intruder dimension check planned = +0.00; not planned = +0.05
  G-F2 knowledge-preservation assert planned (if corda_mode=true) =
  +0.00; not planned = +0.05
  (If corda_mode=false, G-F2 contributes +0.00 — not applicable.)

SUM = sum of contributions, clamp [0, 1].

CONVERGENCE CHECK (P9 — homeostatic regulation):
- Metric ≤ 0.10: near converged (training-ready).
- Metric ≤ 0.10 AND relative improvement ≥ 5% from previous_metric:
  converged.
- If metric > 0.10 OR improvement < 5%: not converged — identify
  blockers.
- Blockers = specific gate failures (from `gate_results`), unresolved
  critical/high findings (with config evidence), stagnation (no new
  regression proposed despite finding evidence), contract gaps
  (math/QLoRA/data/forgetting gates uncovered).

CNS SPAN (P9):
- `cns.lora.convergence` is registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit span unconditionally:
  (`target: "cns.lora.convergence"`, message: `"CNS"`,
  operation: `"convergence_check"`, metric, previous_metric,
  improvement_pct, blockers: [...], replicant_host, latency_ms).

OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON):
`{convergence_metric, previous_metric, improvement_pct, converged:
bool, blockers: [...], gate_results_summary: {math_pass_count,
qlora_pass_count, data_pass_count, forgetting_pass_count},
existing_regressions_count, proposed_regressions_count,
unresolved_critical, unresolved_high, qlora_mode, corda_mode,
replicant_host, cns_span_emitted: true}`.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal): Who = replicant host; What = convergence
metric; Where = audit cycle / workspace; When = pre-training cycle;
Why = P9 observable self-correction / P7 evolutionary progress; How =
compute metric + check improvement + emit CNS span (or note gap) +
identify blockers. All 6 present.

MINIMAL: One template (`KnowAct`); no extra computation; uses
evidence from previous phases only; no synthetic metrics.
EVIDENCE-BACKED ONLY (P8): Metric dimensions use concrete counts
from `findings`, `gate_results` (verified by config evidence),
`existing_regressions` (actual YAML file count),
`proposed_regressions` (actual proposal count from current cycle).
No fabricated numbers.
EVOLUTIONARY (P7): Blockers propose concrete next steps (e.g., "set
`use_rslora=True` for r=128 config", "add `preprocess_loraga()`
call before training", "plan intruder-dimension check post-
training") based on real config evidence — not speculative.
OCAP BOUNDARY (P4): Metric computed from workspace config evidence
only; no actual training execution; no model download; no network
calls to HuggingFace Hub without explicit consent (P2).
CNS REGULATION (P9): Span emitted unconditionally — namespace
registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
(`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`).
REPLICANT HOST (P12): `replicant_host` mandatory.
VISIBILITY (P11): Metric output public; no hidden training posture.
SAFETY FLOOR (P3.1): Training convergence protects Generative Space
— unconverged metric indicates training-config risk.
SEMANTIC GROUNDING (P8): Every blocker references concrete evidence
(config path, parameter, gate ID, source citation).

SOURCE REFERENCES (P8 — concrete):
- LoRA: arXiv:2106.09685 (arxiv.org/abs/2106.09685) — §4.1 init,
  §4.2 merge, §4.1 α/r scaling, §4.3 rank budget, Table 5 param count.
- QLoRA: arXiv:2305.14314 (arxiv.org/abs/2305.14314) — §3 NF4,
  double quant, paged optim, bf16 compute; §5 data quality; §6 eval.
- rsLoRA: arXiv:2312.03732 (arxiv.org/abs/2312.03732) — α/√r for
  high rank.
- DoRA: arXiv:2402.09353 (arxiv.org/abs/2402.09353) — magnitude/
  direction decomposition.
- PiSSA: arXiv:2404.02948 (arxiv.org/abs/2404.02948) — SVD init,
  fast convergence.
- LoRA-GA: arXiv:2407.05000 (arxiv.org/abs/2407.05000) — gradient
  SVD init, 2-4× faster convergence.
- AdaLoRA: arXiv:2303.10512 (arxiv.org/abs/2303.10512) — dynamic
  rank (not default; overhead caveat).
- Razin et al. (intruder dimensions): arXiv:2410.21228
  (arxiv.org/abs/2410.21228) — LoRA ≠ full fine-tune; structured
  forgetting.
- PEFT v0.19.0: huggingface.co/docs/peft/v0.19.0/package_reference/lora
  — LoraConfig field docstrings.
- `security/regressions/README.md` (regression format and ratchet
  lifecycle).
- `security/regressions/` (actual regression library — read as
  input).
- `kali-audit` SKILL.md (§Defense-in-Depth Layer Catalog, §Relationship
  to adversarial-red-team, §Constraints — complements this skill).
- `tdd` SKILL.md (§Relationship — training-loop code vs training
  config).
- `bug-hunt` SKILL.md (§bug-hunt-convergence-check — convergence
  metric computation pattern adopted).
- `supply-chain-sentinel` SKILL.md (§convergence-check — parallel
  pre-flight gate convergence pattern).
- `principles.md` (§P5 Essentialism, §P7 Evolutionary, §P8 Semantic
  Grounding, §P9 Homeostatic Self-Regulation, §P12 Replicant Host
  Mandate).

REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): Registry manifest + `.j2` templates
are canonical. SKILL.md derived. If conflict, registry wins.
PUBLIC VISIBILITY: `visibility: public` — no hidden audit controls.
NO FABRICATION: Metric computed from evidence counts only. Blockers
derived from actual `findings`, `gate_results`,
`proposed_regressions`. No synthetic config references. No synthetic
regression counts.
CONVERGENCE INDEPENDENT: Separate `.j2` template; does not duplicate
`report` phase logic. Uses `findings` and `gate_results` from
`audit-config` (or from previous audit cycle if persistence is
enabled by user). If no previous cycle, assumes `previous_metric =
1.0` (initial state) — explicit assumption, not hidden.
CNS SPAN EMITTED: `cns.lora.convergence` is registered, so the span
is always emitted. Output states `cns_span_emitted: true`.
MINIMAL ARTIFACT: This template produces exactly the metric, verdict,
and blockers — no extra synthesis (that is `report.j2`
responsibility).
